<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Havusin on 04-02-2001 06:32 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">At 54 it was

1. Comp Heal
2. Remedy
3. Celestial
4. Stun (level 5)
5. Dmg Stun
6. Root/Buff Rotate Slot
7. DA
8. DB

Replying to the person that asked about Comp Heal always being memmed, yes.  Ive had it memmed since I got it.  Even in their 40s, Warriors are going to have 2k+ Hps with buffs.  Healing them at 20-30% health still makes comp your best heal then.  Considering at 54, you are going to be grouping with 3k-5k total Hp tanks, I couldnt imagine keeping one alive without burning mana constantly.  Hell, I even use Comp on Rangers, Pallies, Sks, and sometimes rogues.  Granted, sometimes this takes "Teaching" a group that it is so much easier on a cleric if one person holds aggro.  Those groups with multiple tanks, both around 50% health are a bit tricky, but I will usually ask one of them to take the taunt, throw a celestial on the off tank, and use comp/remedy for 90% of the time that I am grouped with them.

I didnt really like my lineup at 54. I hate divine light, period.  Its 350 mana, and I felt like casting that spell is being lazy.  I mean, for 50 more mana, you can use comp.  The only times I use DL is on raids, because comp is a bit too slow because of lag or you are dealing with a mob that can quad for 400+.  Besides that, the only time I have used DL is in a group that isnt doing a good job in keeping aggro off of the enchanter.

Regarding DA, I dont think I could play without it, had it memmed since level one.  On multiple pulls now, I will use Stun Command (55) and then move off to the side, click one of my divines, and let the enchanter mez the extras off one by one. Like many others, in the rare situation where I would need to gate out, I simply mem while divine.  DA saves me mana in controlling aggro, in addition to keeping me alive countless times, Ive used it even more since the aggro changes because of the aggro I have been generating on big boss hunts.

At 57, things have changed a bit, but still primarily the same. For grouping.

1. Comp Heal
2. Remedy
3. Celestial
4. MoK
5. Stun (level 5)/Root/Buff Rotate Slot
6. Stun Command
7. DA.
8. DB

This will probably be the setup I use until 60, only change I see is changing from celestial healing to elixir.

Raids it changes a bit, WOR makes trak a joke imho, and again, I mem DL on raids simply for lag reasons.

-hav
\|/</TEXTAREA>
